                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed"
                                    type="button"
                                    data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                    data-bs-target="#collapseThree"
                                    aria-expanded="false"
                                    aria-controls="collapseThree">
                                Is it possible to release legacy Android applications on other platforms?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseThree"
                             class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                             aria-labelledby="headingThree"
                             data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Absolutely! You can modify, upgrade, customize and fix bugs for your legacy Android applications
                                and release them on other platforms. Android offers an easy multi-platform release with almost nil
                                compatibility issues whilst retaining the initial framework as it is.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFour">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed"
                                    type="button"
                                    data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                    data-bs-target="#collapseFour"
                                    aria-expanded="false"
                                    aria-controls="collapseFour">
                                What is the memory management offered on Android?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseFour"
                             class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                             aria-labelledby="headingFour"
                             data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Android is designed for on-the-go cellular or smaller devices/screens. Therefore, the power
                                consumption has to be reduced to the minimum. Android manages memory to suspend operations when
                                any application is not in use. Also, it does not use battery power or CPU resources while any
                                application is not in use. On Android, the system invisibly and automatically starts closing
                                inactive processes.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFive">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed"
                                    type="button"
                                    data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                    data-bs-target="#collapseFive"
                                    aria-expanded="false"
                                    aria-controls="collapseFive">
                                Are Android apps secure?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseFive"
                             class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                             aria-labelledby="headingFive"
                             data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Android applications offer a great deal of security with the support of an ecosystem. Android apps
                                run in an isolated area where the rest of the system doesn’t have automatic access to the
                                applications, the user has to explicitly grant these permissions. This isolated area is called a
                                sandbox. Android uses many such means to keep user data secure. And is constantly adding on to its
                                security tech stack.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingSix">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed"
                                    type="button"
                                    data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                    data-bs-target="#collapseSix"
                                    aria-expanded="false"
                                    aria-controls="collapseSix">
                                Are Android applications prone to piracy?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseSix"
                             class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                             aria-labelledby="headingSix"
                             data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                This is a concern for most paid applications, as Android applications are prone to piracy.
                                Especially paid applications. But Android does offer encryption to applications to prevent this
                                from happening. And does have a system in place to warn users about third party, dubious
                                applications.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
